  "texts": [
    "This raises privacy concerns in the way data is extracted, aggregated, and granular predictions are eventually publicly released.",
    "Examples of practices which emerge from the marriage between Big Data and polling include: the extraction of behavioural information from real-time streams of social media data, such as, YouTube or Reddit; the creation and exploitation of fully identifiable databases of registered voters (e.g., VR files in the US), containing over 1, 000 features per individual, and encompassing census-like socio-demographic information; the non-consensual merging and augmentation of identifiable online information with commercial data; and the generation of voting predictions for a specific neighborhood.",
    "We argue that AI polls need not be privacy violating when it comes to information privacy.",
    "We will tackle the question of political privacy as decisional autonomy in the following section.",
    "The protection of information privacy is possible under two conditions: (a) that the emergent AI polling industry adopts best practices around the ethical treatment of sensitive data; (b) that the industry's predictive output, and in particular its level of analysis, be constrained by regulations."
  ],
